{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013fUHXDUZUMKu7dJLyLuMXi","type":"tool_result","content":"   150→- [ ] Countdown timer showing betting window remaining\n   151→- [ ] Resolution animation: GREEN/RED result display\n   152→- [ ] Clear indication of round outcome and player result\n   153→\n   154→---\n   155→\n   156→## On-Chain Architecture\n   157→\n   158→### Account PDAs\n   159→\n   160→| Account | Seeds | Purpose |\n   161→|---------|-------|---------|\n   162→| `CloseCallConfig` | `[\"closecall_config\"]` | Treasury, timing params, pause flag, max entries per side, Pyth feed address |\n   163→| `CloseCallRound` | `[\"cc_round\", round_id]` | Per-round: entries (green/red), pool totals, open/close prices, outcome, phase |\n   164→\n   165→Two PDA types. Same minimal pattern as coinflip.\n   166→\n   167→### Instructions\n   168→\n   169→| Instruction | Who calls | What it does |\n   170→|-------------|-----------|-------------|\n   171→| `initialize_config` | Authority | One-time config setup (treasury, timing, Pyth feed) |\n   172→| `create_round` | Server | Creates round PDA, stores Pyth open price, pays rent |\n   173→| `place_bet` | Player | Deposits SOL into round PDA, picks GREEN or RED |\n   174→| `settle_round` | Server | Reads Pyth close price on-chain, determines outcome: pay winners or refund all |\n   175→| `timeout_refund` | Anyone | Permissionless after resolve_deadline — refunds all players |\n   176→| `force_close` | Authority | Emergency admin close — refunds all |\n   177→\n   178→6 instructions.\n   179→\n   180→### Fee Model\n   181→\n   182→Fee = 3% of total pool, collected at settlement of decisive rounds.\n   183→- Decisive round: `fee = 3% × total_pool`. Winners share `net_pool = total_pool - fee`.\n   184→- Invalid round: NO fee. Full refund to all players.\n   185→- Example: Green pool 7 SOL + Red pool 3 SOL = 10 SOL total. Green wins. Fee = 0.30 SOL. Green bettors share 9.70 SOL proportionally.\n   186→\n   187→### Shared Crate Reuse\n   188→\n   189→From `solana/shared/src/`:\n   190→- `escrow.rs` — `transfer_lamports_from_pda`, `transfer_lamports_to_pda`, `close_pda`\n   191→- `fees.rs` — `calculate_net_payout`, `split_fee`\n   192→- `wager.rs` — `validate_wager`\n   193→- `timeout.rs` — `is_expired`\n   194→- `pause.rs` — `check_not_paused`\n   195→\n   196→Program reads Pyth push oracle price accounts directly (no SDK dependency — manual parser in `pyth.rs`).\n   197→\n   198→---\n   199→\n   200→## Success Criteria\n   201→\n   202→- A player can bet on candle direction, watch it resolve, and receive proportional auto-payout\n   203→- Pari-mutuel payouts are mathematically correct for all pool distributions\n   204→- Invalid rounds (equal price, one-sided, single player) refund fully with no fee\n   205→- Settlement is idempotent and atomic\n   206→- Price data is from a verifiable oracle source (Pyth Network)\n   207→- Timeout refund protects players if backend fails\n   208→\n   209→---\n   210→\n   211→## Dependencies\n   212→\n   213→- Pyth Network price feed integration (on-chain `PriceUpdateV2` account)\n   214→- Platform flexible betting system\n   215→- On-chain settlement infrastructure (shared crate)\n   216→- Real-time WebSocket for live price display (existing `packages/price-feeds`)\n   217→\n   218→## Assumptions\n   219→\n   220→- BTC/USD is the only asset at launch\n   221→- Pyth Network provides sufficiently low-latency price data for 1-minute candles\n   222→- 64 max entries per round fits within single-transaction compute budget for auto-payout\n   223→- Backend clock worker reliably creates and settles rounds at minute boundaries\n   224→\n   225→---\n   226→\n   227→## Validation Plan\n   228→\n   229→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   230→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   231→| 1 | Round aligned to minute boundaries | Observe round transitions at :00 marks | Timestamps in logs |\n   232→| 2 | Pari-mutuel payout correct | Multi-player round, verify proportional payouts | Calculation proof |\n   233→| 3 | Equal price triggers full refund | Force equal-price condition | All bets returned, no fee |\n   234→| 4 | One-sided pool triggers refund | All bets on one side | All bets returned, no fee |\n   235→| 5 | Settlement idempotent | Attempt double-settle | Error response proof |\n   236→| 6 | Price from Pyth verified | Compare on-chain price vs Pyth feed | Price comparison |\n   237→| 7 | Timeout refund works | Let resolve deadline expire | Permissionless refund succeeds |\n   238→| 8 | Auto-payout delivered | Win a round | Lamports arrive without claim tx |\n   239→\n   240→---\n   241→\n   242→## Completion Signal\n   243→\n   244→### Implementation Checklist\n   245→\n   246→Items are ordered by dependency. Each unchecked item = one autonomous iteration.\n   247→\n   248→#### On-chain program — DONE (iteration 0)\n   249→- [x] [on-chain] CloseCallConfig + CloseCallRound PDAs, all 6 instructions, fee calc, invalid round handling, manual Pyth PriceUpdateV2 parser (`pyth.rs`)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TVrhQDzjNAbznhSJSQdJTY","session_id":"8567a258-d736-4e38-97a8-6f64b6a42fd3","uuid":"102d0c07-ce34-422c-af02-30a51aaab4b0"}
