{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017TgsJaBmRzsi276rv1fSSw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all three files. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nBased on reading the three backend worker files, here's what the clock worker has available:\n\n### **DecodedCloseCallRound Interface** (account-decoder.ts, lines 125-142)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface DecodedCloseCallRound {\n  roundId: number[];                    // 8-byte buffer\n  server: PublicKey;\n  phase: number;                        // 0=Open, 1=Settled, 2=Refunded\n  greenEntries: Array<{ player: PublicKey; amountLamports: bigint }>;\n  redEntries: Array<{ player: PublicKey; amountLamports: bigint }>;\n  greenPool: bigint;\n  redPool: bigint;\n  openPrice: bigint;                    // Pyth price (i64)\n  openPriceExpo: number;                // Pyth exponent (i32)\n  closePrice: bigint;\n  createdAt: bigint;                    // Timestamp\n  bettingEndsAt: bigint;                // Timestamp\n  resolveDeadline: bigint;              // Timestamp\n  outcome: number;                      // 0=Pending, 1=Green, 2=Red, 3=Refund\n  totalFee: bigint;\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n### **Clock Worker Data Availability** (closecall-clock.ts)\n\n**During settlement (lines 198-308):**\n- `activeRoundId` — 8-byte buffer (generated randomly at creation, line 315)\n- `activeRoundPda` — PublicKey of the round PDA\n- Full decoded `DecodedCloseCallRound` object (line 217)\n- Pyth close price from on-chain account (lines 132-140)\n- Treasury address from CloseCallConfig (lines 143-152)\n\n**Available for DB storage from decoded round:**\n- `roundId` (as hex string: `activeRoundId.toString(\"hex\")`)\n- `server` (PublicKey)\n- `phase` (number)\n- Entry arrays with players + amounts (both green and red)\n- Pool totals, open/close prices, timestamps\n- Betting window end time\n- Resolve deadline\n- Current outcome state\n\n**Pre-settlement calculation (lines 247-257):**\nThe clock worker pre-determines outcome **before** settlement:\n- Counts green/red entries\n- Checks if both sides exist\n- Checks if price changed from open\n- Decides: refund vs green win vs red win\n\n**Transaction data passed to settlement (lines 274-280):**\n- `roundId` (Buffer)\n- `pythPriceAccount` (PublicKey)\n- `treasury` (PublicKey)\n- `remainingAccounts` — array of winner/refund player PublicKeys (pre-computed based on outcome)\n\n### **Round Tracking in Clock Worker** (lines 79-81)\n\n```typescript\nlet activeRoundId: Buffer | null = null;        // 8-byte roundId\nlet activeRoundPda: PublicKey | null = null;    // Derived PDA\n```\n\n- **On start**: `discoverActiveRound()` scans all CloseCallRound accounts, filters by phase=OPEN and server match (lines 157-188)\n- **After create**: Sets both variables to newly created round (lines 326-327)\n- **After settle**: Clears both to null (lines 295-296, 304-305)\n\n### **Available for DB at Key Points**\n\n| Point | Data Available |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| **Round Creation** | roundId (8-byte buffer), roundPda, openPrice from Pyth, timestamp |\n| **During Active Round** | Full decoded round state (all entries, pools, phase) |\n| **At Settlement Decision** | outcome type (refund/green/red), greenCount, redCount, pythPrice.price, openPrice |\n| **After Settlement** | entriesPerSide arrays, winning player list (or all players for refund), settle tx signature |\n| **On Restart** | Can recover activeRound via discriminator scan + phase check |\n\n### **Key Constraints**\n\n- Round PDA seeds: `[\"cc_round\", roundId]` (line 533)\n- Phase values: Open=0, Settled=1, Refunded=2 (line 49-54)\n- Outcome values: Pending=0, Green=1, Red=2, Refund=3 (line 57-64)\n- Clock ticks every minute, aligned 2s after minute boundary (lines 40-41, 88-92)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aedc5a13e93d12dce (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 52113\ntool_