{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VpWjxE7a4EBZaYcwWaxGXR","type":"tool_result","content":"   250→- [x] [test] Bankrun tests: 20 tests covering all instructions + edge cases (equal price, one-sided, single player, max entries, timeout)\n   251→\n   252→#### Phase 1: Pyth + Anchor Client\n   253→- [x] [on-chain] Verify `pyth.rs` parser works with Pyth push oracle price accounts on devnet (BTC/USD feed). If the devnet Pyth accounts use a different format than PriceUpdateV2, adapt the parser. Find the correct Pyth BTC/USD price account address for devnet. Update bankrun tests with correct mock format if changed. Run `anchor build` + bankrun tests to confirm. (done: iteration 1)\n   254→- [x] [engine] Copy `solana/target/idl/closecall.json` and `solana/target/types/closecall.ts` into `packages/anchor-client/src/`. Add `closecall` to the barrel export in `packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts` following the exact pattern used for coinflip and lordofrngs (IDL JSON import + type re-export). Add `CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID` constant to `packages/config/`. Run `pnpm lint` in the anchor-client package to confirm no errors. (done: iteration 2)\n   255→\n   256→#### Phase 2: Backend\n   257→- [x] [backend] In `services/backend/src/worker/account-decoder.ts`, add `DecodedCloseCallRound` and `DecodedCloseCallConfig` interfaces + decoder functions using `BorshAccountsCoder` from the closecall IDL. Follow the exact pattern of the existing coinflip/lordofrngs decoders (bnToBigInt conversion, phase enum mapping). Export from module. Run `pnpm lint` to confirm. (done: iteration 3)\n   258→- [x] [backend] In `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`, add closecall settlement functions: `buildCreateRoundTx(roundId, pythPriceAccount)`, `buildSettleRoundTx(roundId, pythPriceAccount, winnerAccounts)`, `buildTimeoutRefundTx(roundId, playerAccounts)`. The backend reads the Pyth push oracle price account via `connection.getAccountInfo()` — no Hermes fetch needed. Follow the existing coinflip/lordofrngs settle pattern. Run `pnpm lint` to confirm. (done: iteration 4)\n   259→- [x] [backend] Create `services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` — a `CloseCallClockWorker` that runs on minute-boundary intervals. Each tick: (1) read Pyth BTC/USD push oracle price from Solana via RPC, (2) settle the previous round if it exists and candle has closed (call `buildSettleRoundTx`), (3) create a new round (call `buildCreateRoundTx` with open price from Pyth account). Use the existing `retry.ts` pattern for tx submission. Handle edge cases: no previous round, settlement failure (log + continue). Export worker class. (done: iteration 5)\n   260→- [ ] [backend] Extend DB: add `game = \"closecall\"` support to the `rounds` table (or create a new `closecall_rounds` table if schema differs significantly). Store: round_id, open_price, close_price, outcome, green_pool, red_pool, fee, created_at, settled_at, tx_signature. Add API routes: `GET /closecall/current-round` (returns active round + pool state), `GET /closecall/history` (last 20 settled rounds). Extend `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:roundId` to support closecall rounds. Follow the existing route creation pattern in `services/backend/src/routes/`.\n   261→- [ ] [backend] Wire the `CloseCallClockWorker` into `services/backend/src/index.ts`: import, instantiate with config (Pyth BTC/USD account address, server keypair, connection, DB), start on backend boot. Add `PYTH_BTC_USD_ACCOUNT` env var to `.env` and config loading. Run `pnpm lint` across backend to confirm. Verify the backend starts without errors (even if clock worker won't find rounds on devnet yet).\n   262→\n   263→#### Phase 3: Devnet Deploy\n   264→- [ ] [deploy] Deploy closecall program to devnet: `anchor deploy --provider.cluster devnet -p closecall`. Run `initialize_config` on devnet (treasury from `.env.devnet`, Pyth BTC/USD feed ID for devnet, 30s betting window, 32 max entries per side). Add `VITE_CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID=8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA` to `.env.devnet`. Verify by calling `create_round` + `place_bet` + `settle_round` manually against real Pyth prices.\n   265→\n   266→#### Phase 4: Frontend Integration (existing mock scaffolding → real)\n   267→\n   268→Note: FE scaffolding already exists at `apps/platform/src/features/close-call/` with mock simulation. Route, sidebar nav entry, and component structure are already in place. These iterations swap mocks for real backend/on-chain integration.\n   269→\n   270→- [ ] [frontend] Update `features/close-call/types.ts`: remove DOJI threshold, carryover, commit-reveal fields (`seedHash`, `serverSeed`, `blockHash`, `carryoverAmount`). Remove `claimPayout` from context actions (auto-payout). Fix constants: `BETTING_WINDOW_MS = 30000` (was 10000), `MIN_BET_AMOUNT` to 0.001 SOL, `MAX_BET_AMOUNT` to 100 SOL. Align `RoundPhase` with on-chain `CloseCallPhase` (Open/Settled/Refunded). Align `CandleOutcome` — remove \"doji\", add \"refund\". Update `PoolState` to match on-chain `green_pool`/`red_pool` fields. Run `pnpm lint` to confirm no type errors cascade.\n   271→- [ ] [frontend] Rewrite `features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`: replace `mock-simulation.ts` imports with real backend API calls (`GET /closecall/current-round` for active round + pools, `GET /closecall/history` for recent rounds). Poll current round every 2s (or use existing event subscription pattern from coinflip). Read Pyth BTC/USD price for chart via existing `packages/price-feeds` `usePriceSubscription(\"BTC\")`. Remove `claimPayout()`, remove carryover/jackpot state. Keep `placeBet()` as a stub that calls the wallet tx (wired in next iteration). Run `pnpm lint` + verify page loads without crash.\n   272→- [ ] [frontend] Wire wallet integration for `place_bet`: in `CloseCallContext.tsx`, implement `placeBet()` to build and send a `place_bet` transaction using the closecall IDL from `packages/anchor-client`. Follow the exact pattern used in coinflip for tx building + signing via `useWallet()`. Handle errors: insufficient balance → toast, betting closed race → toast + refresh round, tx failure → toast with retry. On successful bet, optimistically update `userBet` in context, then confirm via next poll. Remove `mock-simulation.ts` and `payout-calculator.ts` if fully replaced. Run `pnpm lint`.\n   273→- [ ] [frontend] Add `/close-call/:roundId` deep-link page: create `pages/CloseCallRoundPage.tsx` (follow pattern of `CoinflipRoundPage`). Fetch round data from `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:roundId`. Display: open price, close price, outcome (Green/Red/Refund), green pool, red pool, total pool, fee collected, entries list, settlement tx signature. Add route to `App.tsx`. Link from round history list. Run `pnpm lint`.\n   274→\n   275→#### Phase 5: Testing\n   276→- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for close-call pages. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) → commit. **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) → save diff images, describe in history.md, output blocker. **FAIL** (broken layout) → fix code, don't update baselines.\n   277→- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   278→- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   279→- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is in scope, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n   280→\n   281→### Testing Requirements\n   282→\n   283→The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   284→\n   285→#### Code Quality\n   286→- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   287→- [x] New bankrun tests for all 6 instructions (done: iteration 0)\n   288→- [x] New tests for pari-mutuel payout calculations (done: iteration 0)\n   289→- [x] New tests for invalid round conditions (done: iteration 0)\n   290→- [ ] No lint errors\n   291→\n   292→#### Functional Verification\n   293→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   294→- [ ] Edge cases: equal price, single-sided pool, max entries reached, timeout refund\n   295→- [ ] Settlement idempotency verified\n   296→- [ ] Auto-payout delivers correct amounts\n   297→\n   298→#### Visual Verification\n   299→- [ ] Chart and betting UI correct on desktop"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TVrhQDzjNAbznhSJSQdJTY","session_id":"8567a258-d736-4e38-97a8-6f64b6a42fd3","uuid":"00e1580c-9bdc-4e9a-a6e1-12502bf50074"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a5f2da5df7ca6cc09","tool_use_id":"toolu_01TVrhQDzjNAbznhSJSQdJTY","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore backend DB schema","usage":{"total_tokens":70966,"tool_uses":34,"duration_ms":106221},"uuid":"0f6e622c-c1e1-478e-ad58-ba9eed3bb595","session_id":"8567a258-d736-4e38-97a8-6f64b6a42fd3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TVrhQDzjNAbznhSJSQdJTY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the backend service, here's the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Backend Service Architecture - Complete Overview\n\n### 1. Database Setup\n\n**Type**: PostgreSQL (via `postgres` npm package v3.4.0)\n- **ORM/Driver**: Raw postgres.js (typed SQL queries, no ORM)\n- **Configuration**: \n  - Connection via `DATABASE_URL` environment variable\n  - Optional schema support via `DB_SCHEMA` env var (applies via URL search params)\n  - File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n\n**Migration System**:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n- Migrations stored in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/`\n- Named with numeric version prefix (e.g., `001_init.sql`, `002_auth_sessions.sql`)\n- Tracks applied migrations in `_migrations` table\n- Each migration runs in a transaction (atomic)\n- Command: `tsx src/migrate.ts` or `tsx src/migrate.ts status`\n\n### 2. Rounds Table Schema\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql`\n\n**Current Schema** (after migration 003):\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE rounds (\n  pda            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,           -- Match/Round PDA (unique identifier)\n  game           TEXT NOT NULL,              -- 'coinflip', 'lord', or 'closecall'\n  creator        TEXT NOT NULL,              -- Player wallet address\n  server_key     TEXT NOT NULL,              -- Server keypair public key\n  secret         BYTEA NOT NULL,             -- 32-byte secret (commit-reveal games)\n  commitment     BYTEA NOT NULL,             -- SHA256(secret)\n  amount_lamports BIGINT NOT NULL,           -- Wager amount in lamports (replaces tier)\n  side           SMALLINT NOT NULL,          -- Prediction: 0 or 1 for coinflip, 0 for lord/closecall\n  match_id       TEXT NOT NULL,              -- 16-char hex string (8-byte random backend-generated)\n  phase          TEXT NOT NULL,              -- 'created' | 'locked' | 'settling' | 'settled' | 'expired'\n  target_slot    BIGINT,                     -- Slot when match was detected (for entropy resolution)\n  settle_tx      TEXT,                       -- Settlement transaction signature\n  settle_attempts INT DEFAULT 0,              -- Retry counter\n  result_hash    BYTEA,                      -- Final entropy hash (settled rounds only)\n  result_side    SMALLINT,                   -- Outcome: 0/1 for coinflip, entry index for lord, NULL for closecall\n  winner         TEXT,                       -- Winner wallet (NULL if refund/no winner)\n  created_at     TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at     TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_rounds_phase` on `phase`\n- `idx_rounds_creator` on `creator`\n- `idx_rounds_match_id` on `match_id` (added in migration 004, used by `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`)\n\n**Key Notes for Close Call**:\n- The shared `rounds` table is used for ALL games (coinflip, lord, closecall)\n- `side` field is 0 for both lord and closecall (not used for side prediction)\n- `result_side` will be NULL for closecall (outcome is determined by Pyth price comparison, not stored here)\n- Phase machine is unidirectional: `created` → `locked` → `settling` → `settled`, or `created` → `expired`\n\n### 3. Database Client Interface\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Key Types**:\n```typescript\nexport type RoundPhase = \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\";\n\nexport interface Round {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  creator: string;\n  server_key: string;\n  secret: Buffer;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amount_lamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  match_id: string;\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  target_slot: string | null;\n  settle_tx: string | null;\n  settle_attempts: number;\n  result_hash: Buffer | null;\n  result_side: number | null;\n  winner: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface InsertRoundParams {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  creator: string;\n  serverKey: string;      // camelCase in params\n  secret: Buffer;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amountLamports: number; // camelCase in params\n  side: number;\n  matchId: string;        // camelCase in params\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods** (all async):\n- `insertRound(params)` - Insert new round, throws on duplicate PDA\n- `getRoundByPda(pda)` - Fetch single round by PDA, returns undefined if not found\n- `getRoundByMatchId(matchId)` - Fetch by 16-char hex matchId\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` - Fetch all rounds in a phase\n- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates?)` - Enforce valid transitions + optional field updates\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload)` - Audit log\n- `getLatestOperatorEvent(pda, eventType)` - Get most recent event of a type\n- `getUnsettledStats()` - Count + age of unsettled rounds\n\n**Operator Events Table**:\n- Records: `id` (BIGSERIAL), `pda`, `event_type`, `payload` (JSONB), `created_at`\n- Used for audit trail: `secret_generated`, `tx_built`, `match_detected`, `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, `settle_retried`, `timeout_detected`\n\n### 4. Routes Structure\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/`\n\n**Files**:\n- `create.ts` - `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` - Creates new coinflip match\n- `lord-create.ts` - `POST /fairness/lord/create` - Creates new lord-of-rngs round\n- `rounds.ts` - `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` and `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda`\n- `auth.ts` - Auth challenge/verification routes (JWT)\n- `health.ts` - Health check endpoint\n\n**Route Registration** (in `index.ts`):\n```typescript\napp.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher}));\napp.route(\"/fairness/lord\", createLordRoutes({db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher}));\napp.route(\"/fairness/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({db}));\n```\n\n### 5. GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId Implementation\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`\n\n**Endpoint**:\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/by-id/:matchId\", async (c) => {\n  const matchId = c.req.param(\"matchId\");\n  // Validate: 16-char hex string\n  if (!/^[0-9a-f]{16}$/i.test(matchId)) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"matchId must be a 16-char hex string\" }, 400);\n  }\n  \n  // Fetch from DB\n  const round = await db.getRoundByMatchId(matchId.toLowerCase());\n  if (!round) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n  }\n  \n  return c.json(await formatRoundResponse(db, round));\n});\n```\n\n**Response Format** (via `formatRoundResponse`):\n```typescript\n{\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;           // \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\"\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  creator: string;\n  commitment: string;     // hex, always included\n  amountLamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  matchId: string;\n  createdAt: ISO string;\n  updatedAt: ISO string;\n  targetSlot?: number;    // Only if not null\n  \n  // Settled rounds ONLY:\n  secret: string;         // hex\n  resultHash: string | null;  // hex\n  resultSide?: number;    // coinflip/lord result (0 or 1, or entry index for lord)\n  winner: string;         // winner wallet\n  settleTx: string;       // tx signature\n  verification: {\n    commitmentCheck: string;\n    resultFormula: string;\n    entropySource: string;\n  };\n  entropy?: string;       // from settle_confirmed event payload\n  payoutAmount?: number;\n  feeAmount?: number;\n  \n  // Lord-only settled fields:\n  winningEntryIndex?: number;\n  winningOffset?: number;\n  totalAmountLamports?: number;\n  rentRefund?: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Special Handling by Game**:\n- **coinflip**: Uses `resultSide` (0 or 1)\n- **lord**: Uses `winningEntryIndex` instead of `resultSide`\n- **closecall**: Will use simple outcome (likely outcome enum or similar)\n\n### 6. Route Creation Pattern\n\nBoth `create.ts` and `lord-create.ts` follow the same pattern:\n\n**Pattern Steps**:\n1. **Validate request body** - type checking and range validation\n2. **Verify JWT wallet** - defense-in-depth check\n3. **Validate public key** - try/catch on PublicKey constructor\n4. **Generate secrets** - `generateSecret()` (32 bytes), `generateMatchId()` (8 bytes)\n5. **Compute commitment** - `SHA256(secret)`\n6. **Derive PDA** - Unique per game (different seeds)\n7. **Check for duplicates** - Query DB before insert (race condition check)\n8. **Build transaction** - Partially-signed TX via `buildCreateMatchTx` or `buildCreateLordRoundTx`\n9. **Insert into DB** - Phase starts as \"created\"\n10. **Insert operator event** - Audit log entry with payload\n11. **Watch PDA** - Subscribe to PDaWatcher for instant join detection\n12. **Return response** - Transaction (base64), PDA, matchId (hex), commitment (hex), lastValidBlockHeight\n\n**Response Structure**:\n```typescript\n{\n  transaction: string;        // base64-serialized, partially-signed TX\n  matchPda: string;           // for coinflip\n  roundPda: string;           // for lord (different field name!)\n  matchId: string;            // 16-char hex\n  commitment: string;         // hex\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Validation Ranges**:\n- `amountLamports`: 1,000,000 to 100,000,000,000 (0.001 to 100 SOL)\n- `side`: 0 or 1 (coinflip only)\n- `wallet`: base58 public key\n\n**Error Handling**:\n- 400: Invalid request body / validation failure\n- 403: Wallet mismatch with JWT\n- 409: Duplicate PDA / race condition\n- 500: Transaction build error\n\n### 7. Transaction Building Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts`\n\n**Pattern**:\n```typescript\nexport async function buildCreateMatchTx(params: BuildCreateMatchTxParams) {\n  // 1. Derive PDAs\n  const [matchPda] = deriveMatchPda(creator, matchId);\n  const [configPda] = deriveConfigPda();\n  \n  // 2. Encode instruction data (discriminator + fields)\n  const data = encodeCreateMatchData(commitment, amountLamports, side, matchId);\n  \n  // 3. Build transaction with instruction\n  const tx = new Transaction();\n  tx.add(new TransactionInstruction({\n    keys: [ /* account list */ ],\n    programId: PROGRAM_ID,\n    data,\n  }));\n  \n  // 4. Fetch recent blockhash\n  const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } = await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n  \n  // 5. Set fee payer and sign (partially)\n  tx.feePayer = creator;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\n  tx.lastValidBlockHeight = lastValidBlockHeight;\n  tx.partialSign(serverKeypair);\n  \n  // 6. Serialize and return\n  const serialized = tx.serialize({ requireAllSignatures: false }).toString(\"base64\");\n  return { transaction: serialized, matchPda, lastValidBlockHeight };\n}\n```\n\n**Key PDAs**:\n- **Coinflip**: `[\"match\", creator, matchId]` → `deriveMatchPda()`\n- **Lord**: `[\"jackpot_round\", matchId]` → `deriveLordRoundPda()`\n- **Closecall**: `[\"cc_round\", roundId]` (to be added)\n\n**Program IDs**:\n- Coinflip: from `coinflipIdl.address`\n- Lord: from `lordIdl.address`\n- Closecall: from `closecallIdl.address` (already imported in tx-builder.ts)\n\n### 8. Middleware Stack\n\n**JWT Auth Middleware** - Applied to `/fairness/*`:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- Sets `c.get(\"wallet\")` from JWT subject\n- Skips `/auth` routes (auth is unauthenticated)\n\n**Rate Limiting Middleware** - Applied to `/fairness/*` and `/auth/*`:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`\n- Per-wallet limits (e.g., 10 requests/min)\n- Global limits (e.g., 100 requests/min)\n- Window: 60 seconds\n\n### 9. Workers and Background Tasks\n\n**Settlement Worker**:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`\n- Polls DB for rounds in \"settling\" phase\n- Watches for slot advancement\n- Triggers settlement when target slot is reached\n\n**PDA Watcher**:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts`\n- WebSocket-based account change listener\n- Detects when a match PDA changes (join event)\n- Updates DB phase to \"locked\" + target_slot\n- Cleans up subscriptions after settlement\n\n**Close Call Clock Worker** (for closecall):\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n- Runs on minute boundaries\n- Settles previous round (reads Pyth price)\n- Creates new round (stores open price from Pyth)\n- **Note**: This is separate from the commit-reveal settlement model\n\n### 10. Key Configuration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n\n**Required Env Vars**:\n- `DATABASE_URL` - Postgres connection string\n- `RPC_URL` - Solana RPC endpoint\n- `WS_RPC_URL` - (optional) WebSocket RPC for PDa watching\n- `SERVER_KEYPAIR` - JSON array of secret key bytes\n- `JWT_SECRET` - (optional, defaults to keypair hash)\n- `SOLANA_CLUSTER` - (default: \"devnet\")\n- `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` - (default: SlotHashes sysvar)\n- Additional: `PORT`, `CHALLENGE_TTL_SECONDS`, `ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL_SECONDS`, etc.\n\n### 11. Entry Point and Route Registration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n**Boot Sequence**:\n1. Load config\n2. Create DB client\n3. Create auth DB\n4. Create Solana connection\n5. Initialize Hono app with CORS\n6. Add request logging middleware\n7. Register `/auth` routes (no JWT required, lighter rate limit)\n8. Create workers (retry settler, PDA watcher, settlement worker)\n9. Register `/fairness/*` routes with JWT + rate limit middleware:\n   - `/fairness/coinflip/create`\n   - `/fairness/lord/create`\n   - `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`\n   - `/fairness/rounds/:pda`\n10. Register `/health` endpoint\n11. Start Hono server\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Close Call Implementation\n\nFor Close Call support, you'll need to:\n\n1. **Database**: The existing `rounds` table works for closecall too. No schema migration needed (store `game = \"closecall\"`, `side = 0`, `result_side = NULL` or use outcome field).\n\n2. **Routes Pattern**: Follow `lord-create.ts` pattern for `POST /fairness/closecall/create`:\n   - Validate request body (wallet, amountLamports, side: 0 or 1 for green/red)\n   - Generate matchId, commitment, secret\n   - Derive PDA: `[\"cc_round\", roundId]` using CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID\n   - Build TX via new `buildCreateCloseCallTx()` function\n   - Insert round into DB with `game: \"closecall\"`\n   - Watch PDA\n\n3. **TX Builder**: Add `buildCreateCloseCallTx()` to `tx-builder.ts` following the coinflip/lord pattern. The closecall program uses a different instruction set and PDAs.\n\n4. **Round Verification**: The `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` endpoint already works for closecall—it queries by matchId regardless of game type. The `formatRoundResponse()` function should handle closecall by checking `round.game === \"closecall\"` and formatting appropriately (outcome instead of resultSide).\n\n5. **Clock Worker**: The existing `closecall-clock.ts` handles round creation/settlement on minute boundaries. It needs to be wired into `index.ts` alongside the settlement worker.\n\n6. **Database Fields**: For closecall, you may want to track additional fields in the future:\n   - `open_price` / `close_price` (for verification)\n   - `green_pool` / `red_pool` (for payout calculation)\n   - `outcome` (Green/Red/Refund)\n   \n   These could be stored in the operator event payload (like lord does for `totalAmountLamports`) rather than adding new columns to `rounds`.\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths Referenced**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/lord-create.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/003_tier_to_amount.sql`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/004_match_id_index.sql`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/package.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/100-close-call/spec.md`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/lib.rs`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/state.rs`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/closecall.json`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5f2da5df7ca6cc09 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76212\ntool_uses: 34\nduration_ms: 106232</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8567a258-d736-4e38-97a8-6f64b6a42fd3","uuid":"7e045c6e-904c-49b0-845d-f3579edbb7e8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the backend service at `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/` to understand:\n1. How the database is set up (SQLite? Postgres? What ORM/driver?)\n2. The existing `rounds` table schema and how coinflip/lordofrngs rounds are stored\n3. How routes are structured in `services/backend/src/routes/`\n4. How `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:roundId` works\n5. The existing route creation patterns\n\nBe thorough - read the DB setup files, schema definitions, existing route files, and any migration files. I need enough detail to add closecall support following the exact same patterns.","agentId":"a5f2da5df7ca6cc09","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the backend service, here's the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Backend Service Architecture - Complete Overview\n\n### 1. Database Setup\n\n**Type**: PostgreSQL (via `postgres` npm package v3.4.0)\n- **ORM/Driver**: Raw postgres.js (typed SQL queries, no ORM)\n- **Configuration**: \n  - Connection via `DATABASE_URL` environment variable\n  - Optional schema support via `DB_SCHEMA` env var (applies via URL search params)\n  - File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n\n**Migration System**:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n- Migrations stored in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/`\n- Named with numeric version prefix (e.g., `001_init.sql`, `002_auth_sessions.sql`)\n- Tracks applied migrations in `_migrations` table\n- Each migration runs in a transaction (atomic)\n- Command: `tsx src/migrate.ts` or `tsx src/migrate.ts status`\n\n### 2. Rounds Table Schema\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql`\n\n**Current Schema** (after migration 003):\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE rounds (\n  pda            TEXT PRIMARY KEY,           -- Match/Round PDA (unique identifier)\n  game           TEXT NOT NULL,              -- 'coinflip', 'lord', or 'closecall'\n  creator        TEXT NOT NULL,              -- Player wallet address\n  server_key     TEXT NOT NULL,              -- Server keypair public key\n  secret         BYTEA NOT NULL,             -- 32-byte secret (commit-reveal games)\n  commitment     BYTEA NOT NULL,             -- SHA256(secret)\n  amount_lamports BIGINT NOT NULL,           -- Wager amount in lamports (replaces tier)\n  side           SMALLINT NOT NULL,          -- Prediction: 0 or 1 for coinflip, 0 for lord/closecall\n  match_id       TEXT NOT NULL,              -- 16-char hex string (8-byte random backend-generated)\n  phase          TEXT NOT NULL,              -- 'created' | 'locked' | 'settling' | 'settled' | 'expired'\n  target_slot    BIGINT,                     -- Slot when match was detected (for entropy resolution)\n  settle_tx      TEXT,                       -- Settlement transaction signature\n  settle_attempts INT DEFAULT 0,              -- Retry counter\n  result_hash    BYTEA,                      -- Final entropy hash (settled rounds only)\n  result_side    SMALLINT,                   -- Outcome: 0/1 for coinflip, entry index for lord, NULL for closecall\n  winner         TEXT,                       -- Winner wallet (NULL if refund/no winner)\n  created_at     TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at     TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_rounds_phase` on `phase`\n- `idx_rounds_creator` on `creator`\n- `idx_rounds_match_id` on `match_id` (added in migration 004, used by `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`)\n\n**Key Notes for Close Call**:\n- The shared `rounds` table is used for ALL games (coinflip, lord, closecall)\n- `side` field is 0 for both lord and closecall (not used for side prediction)\n- `result_side` will be NULL for closecall (outcome is determined by Pyth price comparison, not stored here)\n- Phase machine is unidirectional: `created` → `locked` → `settling` → `settled`, or `created` → `expired`\n\n### 3. Database Client Interface\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Key Types**:\n```typescript\nexport type RoundPhase = \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\";\n\nexport interface Round {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  creator: string;\n  server_key: string;\n  secret: Buffer;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amount_lamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  match_id: string;\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  target_slot: string | null;\n  settle_tx: string | null;\n  settle_attempts: number;\n  result_hash: Buffer | null;\n  result_side: number | null;\n  winner: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface InsertRoundParams {\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;\n  creator: string;\n  serverKey: string;      // camelCase in params\n  secret: Buffer;\n  commitment: Buffer;\n  amountLamports: number; // camelCase in params\n  side: number;\n  matchId: string;        // camelCase in params\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods** (all async):\n- `insertRound(params)` - Insert new round, throws on duplicate PDA\n- `getRoundByPda(pda)` - Fetch single round by PDA, returns undefined if not found\n- `getRoundByMatchId(matchId)` - Fetch by 16-char hex matchId\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` - Fetch all rounds in a phase\n- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates?)` - Enforce valid transitions + optional field updates\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload)` - Audit log\n- `getLatestOperatorEvent(pda, eventType)` - Get most recent event of a type\n- `getUnsettledStats()` - Count + age of unsettled rounds\n\n**Operator Events Table**:\n- Records: `id` (BIGSERIAL), `pda`, `event_type`, `payload` (JSONB), `created_at`\n- Used for audit trail: `secret_generated`, `tx_built`, `match_detected`, `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, `settle_retried`, `timeout_detected`\n\n### 4. Routes Structure\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/`\n\n**Files**:\n- `create.ts` - `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` - Creates new coinflip match\n- `lord-create.ts` - `POST /fairness/lord/create` - Creates new lord-of-rngs round\n- `rounds.ts` - `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` and `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda`\n- `auth.ts` - Auth challenge/verification routes (JWT)\n- `health.ts` - Health check endpoint\n\n**Route Registration** (in `index.ts`):\n```typescript\napp.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher}));\napp.route(\"/fairness/lord\", createLordRoutes({db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher}));\napp.route(\"/fairness/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({db}));\n```\n\n### 5. GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId Implementation\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`\n\n**Endpoint**:\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/by-id/:matchId\", async (c) => {\n  const matchId = c.req.param(\"matchId\");\n  // Validate: 16-char hex string\n  if (!/^[0-9a-f]{16}$/i.test(matchId)) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"matchId must be a 16-char hex string\" }, 400);\n  }\n  \n  // Fetch from DB\n  const round = await db.getRoundByMatchId(matchId.toLowerCase());\n  if (!round) {\n    return c.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n  }\n  \n  return c.json(await formatRoundResponse(db, round));\n});\n```\n\n**Response Format** (via `formatRoundResponse`):\n```typescript\n{\n  pda: string;\n  game: string;           // \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\"\n  phase: RoundPhase;\n  creator: string;\n  commitment: string;     // hex, always included\n  amountLamports: number;\n  side: number;\n  matchId: string;\n  createdAt: ISO string;\n  updatedAt: ISO string;\n  targetSlot?: number;    // Only if not null\n  \n  // Settled rounds ONLY:\n  secret: string;         // hex\n  resultHash: string | null;  // hex\n  resultSide?: number;    // coinflip/lord result (0 or 1, or entry index for lord)\n  winner: string;         // winner wallet\n  settleTx: string;       // tx signature\n  verification: {\n    commitmentCheck: string;\n    resultFormula: string;\n    entropySource: string;\n  };\n  entropy?: string;       // from settle_confirmed event payload\n  payoutAmount?: number;\n  feeAmount?: number;\n  \n  // Lord-only settled fields:\n  winningEntryIndex?: number;\n  winningOffset?: number;\n  totalAmountLamports?: number;\n  rentRefund?: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Special Handling by Game**:\n- **coinflip**: Uses `resultSide` (0 or 1)\n- **lord**: Uses `winningEntryIndex` instead of `resultSide`\n- **closecall**: Will use simple outcome (likely outcome enum or similar)\n\n### 6. Route Creation Pattern\n\nBoth `create.ts` and `lord-create.ts` follow the same pattern:\n\n**Pattern Steps**:\n1. **Validate request body** - type checking and range validation\n2. **Verify JWT wallet** - defense-in-depth check\n3. **Validate public key** - try/catch on PublicKey constructor\n4. **Generate secrets** - `generateSecret()` (32 bytes), `generateMatchId()` (8 bytes)\n5. **Compute commitment** - `SHA256(secret)`\n6. **Derive PDA** - Unique per game (different seeds)\n7. **Check for duplicates** - Query DB before insert (race condition check)\n8. **Build transaction** - Partially-signed TX via `buildCreateMatchTx` or `buildCreateLordRoundTx`\n9. **Insert into DB** - Phase starts as \"created\"\n10. **Insert operator event** - Audit log entry with payload\n11. **Watch PDA** - Subscribe to PDaWatcher for instant join detection\n12. **Return response** - Transaction (base64), PDA, matchId (hex), commitment (hex), lastValidBlockHeight\n\n**Response Structure**:\n```typescript\n{\n  transaction: string;        // base64-serialized, partially-signed TX\n  matchPda: string;           // for coinflip\n  roundPda: string;           // for lord (different field name!)\n  matchId: string;            // 16-char hex\n  commitment: string;         // hex\n  lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Validation Ranges**:\n- `amountLamports`: 1,000,000 to 100,000,000,000 (0.001 to 100 SOL)\n- `side`: 0 or 1 (coinflip only)\n- `wallet`: base58 public key\n\n**Error Handling**:\n- 400: Invalid request body / validation failure\n- 403: Wallet mismatch with JWT\n- 409: Duplicate PDA / race condition\n- 500: Transaction build error\n\n### 7. Transaction Building Pattern\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts`\n\n**Pattern**:\n```typescript\nexport async function buildCreateMatchTx(params: BuildCreateMatchTxParams) {\n  // 1. Derive PDAs\n  const [matchPda] = deriveMatchPda(creator, matchId);\n  const [configPda] = deriveConfigPda();\n  \n  // 2. Encode instruction data (discriminator + fields)\n  const data = encodeCreateMatchData(commitment, amountLamports, side, matchId);\n  \n  // 3. Build transaction with instruction\n  const tx = new Transaction();\n  tx.add(new TransactionInstruction({\n    keys: [ /* account list */ ],\n    programId: PROGRAM_ID,\n    data,\n  }));\n  \n  // 4. Fetch recent blockhash\n  const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } = await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n  \n  // 5. Set fee payer and sign (partially)\n  tx.feePayer = creator;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\n  tx.lastValidBlockHeight = lastValidBlockHeight;\n  tx.partialSign(serverKeypair);\n  \n  // 6. Serialize and return\n  const serialized = tx.serialize({ requireAllSignatures: false }).toString(\"base64\");\n  return { transaction: serialized, matchPda, lastValidBlockHeight };\n}\n```\n\n**Key PDAs**:\n- **Coinflip**: `[\"match\", creator, matchId]` → `deriveMatchPda()`\n- **Lord**: `[\"jackpot_round\", matchId]` → `deriveLordRoundPda()`\n- **Closecall**: `[\"cc_round\", roundId]` (to be added)\n\n**Program IDs**:\n- Coinflip: from `coinflipIdl.address`\n- Lord: from `lordIdl.address`\n- Closecall: from `closecallIdl.address` (already imported in tx-builder.ts)\n\n### 8. Middleware Stack\n\n**JWT Auth Middleware** - Applied to `/fairness/*`:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- Sets `c.get(\"wallet\")` from JWT subject\n- Skips `/auth` routes (auth is unauthenticated)\n\n**Rate Limiting Middleware** - Applied to `/fairness/*` and `/auth/*`:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`\n- Per-wallet limits (e.g., 10 requests/min)\n- Global limits (e.g., 100 requests/min)\n- Window: 60 seconds\n\n### 9. Workers and Background Tasks\n\n**Settlement Worker**:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`\n- Polls DB for rounds in \"settling\" phase\n- Watches for slot advancement\n- Triggers settlement when target slot is reached\n\n**PDA Watcher**:\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts`\n- WebSocket-based account change listener\n- Detects when a match PDA changes (join event)\n- Updates DB phase to \"locked\" + target_slot\n- Cleans up subscriptions after settlement\n\n**Close Call Clock Worker** (for closecall):\n- File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n- Runs on minute boundaries\n- Settles previous round (reads Pyth price)\n- Creates new round (stores open price from Pyth)\n- **Note**: This is separate from the commit-reveal settlement model\n\n### 10. Key Configuration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n\n**Required Env Vars**:\n- `DATABASE_URL` - Postgres connection string\n- `RPC_URL` - Solana RPC endpoint\n- `WS_RPC_URL` - (optional) WebSocket RPC for PDa watching\n- `SERVER_KEYPAIR` - JSON array of secret key bytes\n- `JWT_SECRET` - (optional, defaults to keypair hash)\n- `SOLANA_CLUSTER` - (default: \"devnet\")\n- `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` - (default: SlotHashes sysvar)\n- Additional: `PORT`, `CHALLENGE_TTL_SECONDS`, `ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL_SECONDS`, etc.\n\n### 11. Entry Point and Route Registration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n**Boot Sequence**:\n1. Load config\n2. Create DB client\n3. Create auth DB\n4. Create Solana connection\n5. Initialize Hono app with CORS\n6. Add request logging middleware\n7. Register `/auth` routes (no JWT required, lighter rate limit)\n8. Create workers (retry settler, PDA watcher, settlement worker)\n9. Register `/fairness/*` routes with JWT + rate limit middleware:\n   - `/fairness/coinflip/create`\n   - `/fairness/lord/create`\n   - `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`\n   - `/fairness/rounds/:pda`\n10. Register `/health` endpoint\n11. Start Hono server\n\n---\n\n## Summary for Close Call Implementation\n\nFor Close Call support, you'll need to:\n\n1. **Database**: The existing `rounds` table works for closecall too. No schema migration needed (store `game = \"closecall\"`, `side = 0`, `result_side = NULL` or use outcome field).\n\n2. **Routes Pattern**: Follow `lord-create.ts` pattern for `POST /fairness/closecall/create`:\n   - Validate request body (wallet, amountLamports, side: 0 or 1 for green/red)\n   - Generate matchId, commitment, secret\n   - Derive PDA: `[\"cc_round\", roundId]` using CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID\n   - Build TX via new `buildCreateCloseCallTx()` function\n   - Insert round into DB with `game: \"closecall\"`\n   - Watch PDA\n\n3. **TX Builder**: Add `buildCreateCloseCallTx()` to `tx-builder.ts` following the coinflip/lord pattern. The closecall program uses a different instruction set and PDAs.\n\n4. **Round Verification**: The `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` endpoint already works for closecall—it queries by matchId regardless of game type. The `formatRoundResponse()` function should handle closecall by checking `round.game === \"closecall\"` and formatting appropriately (outcome instead of resultSide).\n\n5. **Clock Worker**: The existing `closecall-clock.ts` handles round creation/settlement on minute boundaries. It needs to be wired into `index.ts` alongside the settlement worker.\n\n6. **Database Fields**: For closecall, you may want to track additional fields in the future:\n   - `open_price` / `close_price` (for verification)\n   - `green_pool` / `red_pool` (for payout calculation)\n   - `outcome` (Green/Red/Refund)\n   \n   These could be stored in the operator event payload (like lord does for `totalAmountLamports`) rather than adding new columns to `rounds`.\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths Referenced**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/lord-create.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/pda-watcher.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/003_tier_to_amount.sql`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/004_match_id_index.sql`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/package.json`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/100-close-call/spec.md`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/lib.rs`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/state.rs`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/closecall.json`"}],"totalDurationMs":106232,"totalTokens":76212,"totalToolUseCount":34,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2746,"cache_read_input_tokens":67886,"output_tokens":5580,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2746},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Reg3CqbxXdLLxV4DrDeaPx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the backend. Let me read the specific files I'll need to modify to implement this checklist item. The key insight is:\n\n1. **Database**: The existing `rounds` table can be used for closecall with `game = \"closecall\"`, but closecall has different semantics. The current schema has fields like `secret`, `commitment`, `side`, `result_side` that are designed for commit-reveal games. Close Call doesn't use commit-reveal, it uses oracle-based settlement. However, the schema uses `NOT NULL` on `secret` and `commitment`, which are required columns. We'd need a migration to handle this, OR we could store dummy values.\n\n\n2. **Schema mismatch**: Close Call is fundamentally different—it's pari-mutuel with multiple players per round and tracks open_price, close_price, outcome, and pool data, whereas the existing `rounds` table stores one row per player-match interaction. Given these significant differences, creating a separate `closecall_rounds` table makes more sense than forcing the data into the existing schema. The spec actually supports creating a new table when the schema differs significantly, so I'll go with a dedicated `closecall_rounds` table instead of making those columns nullable. Now I need to examine the actual files I'm modifying to plan out the exact changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1208,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6417,"cache_read_input_tokens":34711,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6417},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8567a258-d736-4e38-97a8-6f64b6a42fd3","uuid":"554e262f-52a9-4dec-81ab-34446b0ab456"}
